    <note>Xu Yan [7116] Maoshen's [7245] grandfather, Diao Zhan's [1634] son-in-law, Ouyang Xiu's [1384] father-in-law. Li Ruogu [1046] and Han Zong [657] were his son Yuanheng's [3374] fathers-in-law. Yuanheng was Maoshen's [7245] father. The three generations lived in Zhenjiang, Danyang xian, home of the family of Diao, Yan's wife. The daughter married to Ouyang Xiu [1384] died at the age of seventeen, one month after delivering a male child. This son only lived five years. Hunan TZ, 134.6a (jinshi year a guess); Zeng Gong, WJ, 43.1a; Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 62.6b. CBD, 2, 1536.</note>
